1. General Provisions
The tournament will be a Counter-Strike 2 competition, held from February 16-18, 2026 at Estanbul Gaming, Istanbul, Turkey
The competition will be open to the Global World region through the Valve Regional Standings, in accordance with Valve's regional eligibility rules
The tournament will feature two stages: group stage and playoffs, both played offline (on LAN)
Each player must bring their own peripherals (keyboard, mouse, mousepad, sound card, headset & in-ears)
If any player does not have all their equipment and cannot find a solution within 15 minutes from the scheduled match time, that team will be sanctioned with a loss of that match/map
2. Registrations
To register for the tournament, each team must fill out the registration form
The team registration will be handled by a team representative, who must fill in all required fields
The first registered teams will be selected to participate in the event
Only individuals over 13 years of age may register
Teams may make changes to their lineup, but must retain 60% of the initially registered players. Changes within 7 days of the tournament's start must be supported by valid justification
All teams that have not paid for participation before 8:00 PM on February 3rd will be excluded
3. Payment
Payment details will be provided by a tournament official after the registration form is completed
If anyone writes to you about payment outside of official channels, please ignore them and do not respond
Only communicate with verified tournament officials regarding payment matters
4. Tournament format
GSL Format (16 Teams)
All matches are Best of 3 (BO3) format
Winning moves the team forward in the bracket
Losing goes to the lower bracket or elimination
3rd place decider match will be played
Playoffs (Single Elimination)
Single elimination bracket format
All playoff matches are Best of 3 (BO3)
Losing a match results in elimination from the tournament
Seeding based on group stage performance
Server Configuration
Round time: 1:55 minutes
Freeze time: 15 seconds
Buy time: 20 seconds
Overtime start money: $12,500
Overtime mode: BO6
Agent skins are not allowed
Map Pool
Ancient, Overpass, Dust II, Inferno, Mirage, Nuke & Anubis

BO3 Map Veto
1. Team A removes 1 map
2. Team B removes 1 map
3. Team A picks 1 map → Team B chooses side
4. Team B picks 1 map → Team A chooses side
5. Team A removes 1 map
6. Team B removes 1 map
7. Remaining map is the decider (knife round for side)
6. Tactical Pauses
Each team is entitled to 3 tactical pauses per map (30 seconds each)
1 additional tactical pause is granted if the match goes to overtime
All players must keep their Steam status offline while in a match
7. Round Restoration
Round restoration may only be applied if the following conditions are met:

No more than 60 seconds have passed after the end of freeze time
No player has damage taken
The bomb has not been planted
8. Forbidden Actions
The use of any software or hardware that offers an unfair advantage over the opponent is strictly prohibited
It is forbidden to use exploits or bugs present in the game to gain an unfair advantage
Any communication between a participant and anyone not involved in the match is strictly prohibited
The organization reserves the right to apply sanctions for unsportsmanlike or disrespectful behavior
9. Anti-Cheat & VRS
Valve Anti Cheat will be active during all matches
All matches will be recorded and available on HLTV
The competition is compatible with Valve Regional Standings (VRS) system
Teams without VRS points may freely participate
All peripherals subject to admin inspection
10. Prize Distribution
1st Place: $4,000
2nd Place: $2,000
3rd Place: $1,250
4th Place: $750
5th-8th Place: $500 each
Prizes will be distributed within 30 days of tournament conclusion
All prizes subject to applicable taxes
11. Disclaimer
All broadcast rights of the competition belong to the organization
By registering, teams agree to grant image rights of their members to the competition organizer
Tournament admins have final say on all disputes
